    "version": "2026",
    "chapter": "9. Pharmacologic Approaches to Glycemic Treatment",
    "section": "9.6",
    "recommendation_id": "9.6a",
    "text": "If A1C target is not achieved after approximately 3 months of metformin monotherapy, consider combination therapy with a second agent based on patient-specific factors including ASCVD, heart failure, CKD, weight, hypoglycemia risk, and cost.",
