    "version": "2026",
    "chapter": "11. Chronic Kidney Disease and Risk Management",
    "section": "11.3",
    "recommendation_id": "11.3a",
    "text": "A nonsteroidal mineralocorticoid receptor antagonist (finerenone) is recommended for patients with type 2 diabetes and CKD with persistent albuminuria despite maximum tolerated ACE inhibitor or ARB therapy, to reduce CKD progression and cardiovascular events.",
